Configure this outgoing message so it can be transmitted to a neighbor mote
with the specified wakeup interval.
@param 'message_t* ONE msg' Pointer to the message that will be sent
@param intervalMs The receiving node's wakeup interval, in [ms]

Set this this node's radio wakeup interval, in milliseconds. After each interval, the node will wakeup and check for radio activity.
Note: The wakeup interval can be set to 0 to indicate that the radio should stay on all the time but in order to get a startDone this should only be done when the duty-cycling is off (after a stopDone).
@param intervalMs the length of this node's Rx check interval, in [ms]

